            <pb n="3" facs="#f0001"/>
            <p>We have been favored with the annexed transla-<lb break="no"/>tion of a letter from the venerable Baron <hi rendition="#k">Hum-<lb break="no"/>boldt:</hi>
            </p>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <div n="2">
                <salute>
                    <hi rendition="#k">Lorin Blodget,</hi> Esq., <hi rendition="#i">Washington:</hi>
                </salute>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#k">Sir:</hi> I am very sensible of the honor you have done<lb break="yes"/>me in communicating your important work on the Distri-<lb break="no"/>bution of Heat throughout the vast extent of the United<lb break="yes"/>States.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>When I returned from my expedition to the north of<lb break="yes"/>Asia, near the close of 1829, I proposed to the Academy<lb break="yes"/>of St. Petersburgh to establish meteorological observato-<lb break="no"/>ries at Moscow, Pekin, Archangel, and in the Caucasus,<lb break="yes"/>and I enlarged upon what had been done in your noble<lb break="yes"/>country since 1822 (under care of Messrs. Lovell &#x0026; Law-<lb break="no"/>son) at a large number of military posts near its extreme<lb break="yes"/>limits.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>This is a most meritorious work to which you have de-<lb break="no"/>voted yourself with so much care and intelligence, in the<lb break="yes"/>graphic representation of climates by the use of isother-<lb break="no"/>mal lines. For it I beg you to accept the expression of<lb break="yes"/>my lively gratitude.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>As it is possible that you may not have received a very<lb break="yes"/>recent memoir of Mr. <hi rendition="#k">dove,</hi> my fellow-member of the<lb break="yes"/>Academy of Berlin, I take the liberty to offer it to you.<lb break="yes"/>This memoir is printed in the Journal of the Geographi-<lb break="no"/>cal Society of Berlin for June, 1856. It will present you<lb break="yes"/>some points for further comparison.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>I renew, my dear sir, assurances of the high conside-<lb break="no"/>ration with which I have the honor to be your very hum-<lb break="no"/>ble and very obedient servant,</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">A. V. HUMBOLDT.</hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rendition="#et">
                        <hi rendition="#k">Berlin, September</hi> 7, 1856.</hi>
                </dateline>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
        </body>
